	[em 
		"Sheerluck
	]em
	" is a trial-and-error game for the Commodore 64 that was published in the May 1990 issue of the 
	[em 
		"Compute's! Gazette
	]em
	". While the title may make it seem like winning comes down to sheer luck, all it takes is a simple process of elimination. You play as a detective whose task is to match criminal names with the right mugshots. At the bottom of the screen is a Truth Meter that grades your choices based on whether you got the right mugshots or if you matched the names and mugshots.
